        "content": "<p>Chapter 5.1 is done with the sole exception of these two inequalities:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">int_frac_sqrt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">√</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⌊√</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">⌋</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">0.9</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">int_frac_sqrt'</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">√</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⌊√</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"bp\">⌋</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">0.09</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>sadly <code>norm_num</code> is the only thing I know that helps with concrete numbers and it doesn't work here. Any ideas? Some more powerful mathlib theorems to use (maybe Taylor expansion of sqrt?)</p>",
